<seg id=1> Six Arabian countries in the Persian Gulf region together with Syria and Egypt appealed to Iraq to abide by the UN's decision on an arms inspection, to avoid what they said would only harm Iraq's protesting civilians. </seg>
<seg id=2> The White House welcomed the declaration and took it as further proof that the Iraqi leader Saddam Hussein was isolated in the world, while most of Iraqis seem to think nothing of the possibility of American led bombing. </seg>
